745
01:06:38,923 --> 01:06:53,714
[SPEAKER_09]: consideration of request by executive director to authorize the write-off of collection losses for vacated rent to be incorporated in the federal and state operating statement for fiscal year ending September 30, 2022 in the amount of $13,082.45 and $4,596 for the federal and state program respectively.

746
01:07:04,254 --> 01:07:23,729
[SPEAKER_02]: So what you have here in front of you is every year we review our tenants accounts receivable and the tenants or former tenants that have vacated we identify those and bring those before the Board of Commissioners to have these amounts officially written off.

747
01:07:23,749 --> 01:07:29,633
[SPEAKER_02]: By voting to write these off it does not prevent us from collecting these funds.

748
01:07:30,934 --> 01:07:31,514
[SPEAKER_02]: Sometimes

749
01:07:33,172 --> 01:07:53,835
[SPEAKER_02]: know somebody one of these tenants or former tenants is you know applying for credit or something to that effect this would show up on the report and in order to rectify that they would have to pay us the total balance and I've had a few instances in Brockton where a tenant former tenant

750
01:07:54,323 --> 01:08:06,673
[SPEAKER_02]: has had to pay a sizable write-off from years before in order to purchase a house of some sort, because that write-off was on their credit report.

751
01:08:06,713 --> 01:08:11,897
[SPEAKER_02]: So even by voting to write these off, we can still collect the funds.

