[SPEAKER_01]: in a good distance from the buildings, but those things have grown.

1306
01:44:21,835 --> 01:44:23,076
[SPEAKER_01]: So just take a ride through.

1307
01:44:23,176 --> 01:44:24,297
[SPEAKER_01]: It's a tree city.

1308
01:44:24,317 --> 01:44:25,037
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah, that's right.

1309
01:44:25,117 --> 01:44:25,877
[SPEAKER_01]: It's a good point.

1310
01:44:26,218 --> 01:44:26,698
[SPEAKER_01]: It's a good point.

1311
01:44:26,718 --> 01:44:27,138
[SPEAKER_01]: Maybe that's why.

1312
01:44:27,218 --> 01:44:28,299
[SPEAKER_08]: I was going to say, get ready for...

1313
01:44:29,491 --> 01:44:30,571
[SPEAKER_08]: some comments from the neighbors.

1314
01:44:30,832 --> 01:44:34,353
[SPEAKER_02]: What did you spend the last three year contract?

1315
01:44:34,713 --> 01:44:35,093
[SPEAKER_01]: You know what?

1316
01:44:35,394 --> 01:44:36,134
[SPEAKER_01]: I'll be honest with you.

1317
01:44:36,154 --> 01:44:36,654
[SPEAKER_01]: I don't know.

1318
01:44:36,934 --> 01:44:42,537
[SPEAKER_01]: But usually these estimates come in based upon what we've spent in the past and what the needs are.

1319
01:44:43,577 --> 01:44:46,999
[SPEAKER_01]: Honestly, I'm going to tell you, I think that we spend less than this.

1320
01:44:47,839 --> 01:44:53,581
[SPEAKER_01]: But I think that was because I don't believe we were as vigilant as maybe we should have been.

1321
01:44:55,062 --> 01:44:57,023
[SPEAKER_01]: And during the pandemic,

1322
01:44:58,086 --> 01:45:03,859
[SPEAKER_01]: This is the answer to during the pandemic, HUD was not coming out and doing inspections.

1323
01:45:04,972 --> 01:45:09,856
[SPEAKER_01]: So while the trees were not damaging the buildings, we didn't have an issue.

1324
01:45:10,496 --> 01:45:14,519
[SPEAKER_01]: But knowing now that they're coming out, and they've been out recently, we need to do something.

1325
01:45:14,539 --> 01:45:15,800
[SPEAKER_01]: Do they come out and make a list?

1326
01:45:16,941 --> 01:45:17,141
[SPEAKER_01]: Yes.

1327
01:45:17,501 --> 01:45:19,343
[SPEAKER_01]: When they come out and do an inspection?

1328
01:45:19,383 --> 01:45:19,523
[SPEAKER_01]: Yes.

1329
01:45:19,703 --> 01:45:25,727
[SPEAKER_01]: At the next meeting, I'm going to let you know where we stood with the most recent REAC inspection.

1330
01:45:26,508 --> 01:45:28,810
[SPEAKER_01]: And REAC is Real Estate Assessment Center.

1331
01:45:29,610 --> 01:45:32,993
[SPEAKER_01]: And they give you a very limited period of time.

1332
01:45:33,453 --> 01:45:35,655
[SPEAKER_01]: Used to be two weeks, now it's 28 days.

1333
01:45:36,415 --> 01:45:37,596
[SPEAKER_01]: Notice that they're going to come out.

1334
01:45:38,517 --> 01:45:43,861
[SPEAKER_01]: And it's a very, very intensive review of the authority.

1335
01:45:44,702 --> 01:45:47,244
[SPEAKER_01]: In the past, we have done very, very well.

1336
01:45:48,305 --> 01:45:49,125
[SPEAKER_01]: We've done very well.

1337
01:45:49,205 --> 01:45:54,950
[SPEAKER_08]: And the way they score is, like, the site issues tend to score high or low, you know?

1338
01:45:55,590 --> 01:45:57,452
[SPEAKER_06]: So, like, cracks in the sidewalks, like, stuff that

1339
01:45:58,425 --> 01:46:01,468
