1340
01:46:01,828 --> 01:46:02,328
[SPEAKER_04]: No, no.

1341
01:46:02,709 --> 01:46:03,329
[SPEAKER_04]: 28 days.

1342
01:46:03,349 --> 01:46:05,811
[SPEAKER_06]: 28, but it used to be two months.

1343
01:46:06,051 --> 01:46:07,652
[SPEAKER_01]: No, it used to be two weeks.

1344
01:46:08,053 --> 01:46:11,476
[SPEAKER_06]: Swayed the score kind of heavily.

1345
01:46:11,776 --> 01:46:21,964
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah, when I know with LaPree, when they came out for LaPree previously, they cited us for growth through the chain link fence from the school department.

1346
01:46:22,236 --> 01:46:22,776
[SPEAKER_07]: Vegetation.

1347
01:46:22,996 --> 01:46:24,137
[SPEAKER_01]: Vegetation, yes.

1348
01:46:25,317 --> 01:46:29,799
[SPEAKER_01]: We successfully appealed that.

1349
01:46:30,660 --> 01:46:35,041
[SPEAKER_01]: They also cited us for a walkway that wasn't shoveled.

1350
01:46:35,702 --> 01:46:40,704
[SPEAKER_01]: And what it was, was the residents decided, well, we don't want to walk down the walkway because that's too long.

1351
01:46:41,104 --> 01:46:42,245
[SPEAKER_01]: So we want to walk this way.

1352
01:46:42,445 --> 01:46:45,866
[SPEAKER_01]: And they created a path that we wouldn't shovel anyway.

1353
01:46:46,546 --> 01:46:47,647
[SPEAKER_01]: We were successful on that.

1354
01:46:48,287 --> 01:46:48,827
[SPEAKER_01]: Things like that.

1355
01:46:49,368 --> 01:46:50,268
[SPEAKER_01]: At Bradley Road,

1356
