1358
01:47:01,091 --> 01:47:08,500
[SPEAKER_01]: And one of the .02 deductions we got was because there wasn't a plunger.

1359
01:47:09,295 --> 01:47:14,180
[SPEAKER_01]: In one of the tubs, the resident had taken the plunger out and it was on a chain.

1360
01:47:14,220 --> 01:47:16,802
[SPEAKER_01]: He took it out and put it in his closet.

1361
01:47:17,102 --> 01:47:20,225
[SPEAKER_08]: Right, so even like tenant hall issues or scoring issues.

1362
01:47:20,345 --> 01:47:31,595
[SPEAKER_01]: It's a very- One of the issues that we recently had was that air conditioners were in bedrooms where there was only one window.

1363
01:47:32,336 --> 01:47:34,558
[SPEAKER_01]: That's an egress issue and we lose points for that.

1364
01:47:35,302 --> 01:47:40,628
[SPEAKER_01]: One of the other issues that I know of, and again, I've only looked at the report briefly, see the sprinkler head?

1365
01:47:41,429 --> 01:47:47,115
[SPEAKER_01]: On that head, there's a circular piece of metal that served no purpose.

1366
01:47:48,056 --> 01:47:51,479
[SPEAKER_01]: There were three that were missing, I think it was in this building.

1367
01:47:52,220 --> 01:47:55,904
[SPEAKER_01]: And we got a company who comes in and inspects that.

1368
01:47:56,827 --> 01:47:58,867
[SPEAKER_01]: And I spoke with Gabe.

1369
01:47:58,907 --> 01:48:07,529
[SPEAKER_01]: We're going out to bid on this, because that company that comes in now is not only going to inspect it, they're going to fix it like we used to have when I was in some of them.

1370
01:48:08,289 --> 01:48:11,349
[SPEAKER_01]: And I anticipated that we had you.

1371
01:48:13,350 --> 01:48:17,451
[SPEAKER_01]: But I'm more than likely to have a more intensive report for you next month.

1372
01:48:18,691 --> 01:48:22,991
[SPEAKER_04]: I know Willis Ave, I think, has the most of the trees.

1373
01:48:23,191 --> 01:48:23,652
[SPEAKER_01]: Oh, yeah.

1374
