1411
01:50:04,319 --> 01:50:04,640
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you.

1412
01:50:07,459 --> 01:50:20,764
[SPEAKER_09]: I have nothing to report because I was supposed to be, they actually did the preservation meeting today and I told them I wasn't going to be able to make both meetings, so I have nothing to report because I'm not there.

1413
01:50:20,784 --> 01:50:34,689
[SPEAKER_01]: David, I met with, like I said earlier, the chair of that committee and we expressed the fact that we have submitted an application to them and that we do need assistance from the city

1414
01:50:35,870 --> 01:50:55,971
[SPEAKER_01]: relative to funding whether it comes from community preservation or opera funds or through the city itself and as I indicated I did submit a some correspondence to the mayor concerning a number of issues that involved in particular walkway and

1415
01:50:57,288 --> 01:50:58,709
[SPEAKER_01]: and affordable housing.

1416
01:50:58,749 --> 01:51:01,170
[SPEAKER_01]: And the mayor has emailed me back and I'm going to respond to her.

1417
01:51:01,731 --> 01:51:04,772
[SPEAKER_01]: But she said she's very supportive of affordable housing.

1418
01:51:05,673 --> 01:51:15,898
[SPEAKER_01]: And while there are legitimate concerns that the mayor may have, that's the reason why I am going to hopefully be meeting with she and her legal counsel fairly soon.

1419
01:51:16,718 --> 01:51:23,742
[SPEAKER_01]: But we do have an application into the Community Preservation Committee and they've been very supportive of us in the past.

1420
01:51:24,475 --> 01:51:31,221
[SPEAKER_01]: They've awarded us $350,000 for pre-development costs at WalkLink, which has helped us get to the point that we're at.

1421
01:51:31,761 --> 01:51:40,129
[SPEAKER_01]: We've got, out of the $15 million, we have approximately $1 to $1.1 million from the state to be able to do that pre-development.

1422
01:51:40,149 --> 01:51:43,912
[SPEAKER_01]: So that's what's taking us to where we are now.

1423
01:51:44,592 --> 01:51:54,357
[SPEAKER_01]: We anticipate the closing on that to be in the, it sounds like it's so far away, but it's not, in the spring to early summer of 24.

1424
01:52:02,444 --> 01:52:08,431
[SPEAKER_01]: We're hopeful that the CPC will see fit to award us more.

1425
01:52:08,731 --> 01:52:13,616
[SPEAKER_01]: We've actually asked for $2.4 million over a three year period of time.

1426
01:52:15,738 --> 01:52:25,446
[SPEAKER_01]: We had a discussion about the city's ability to maybe bond that and give us the 2.4 and have the CPC pay that back, that bond back on an extended period of time.

1427
01:52:25,466 --> 01:52:26,527
[SPEAKER_01]: I don't know that that would work.

1428
01:52:27,187 --> 01:52:31,651
[SPEAKER_01]: But we also discussed they're providing us with the 800,000 this year.

1429
01:52:32,471 --> 01:52:38,816
[SPEAKER_01]: That takes up, Melissa, you would know this better than I, but from what I understand, that takes up a significant amount of the money that they're allotted.

1430
01:52:38,916 --> 01:52:41,578
[SPEAKER_01]: So we'll continue to work with that.

1431
01:52:42,499 --> 01:52:55,034
[SPEAKER_01]: You know, the reason why we're looking for the assistance of the city is because the award of the $15 million from the state was predicated on assistance from the city going forward.

1432
01:52:55,074 --> 01:52:57,577
[SPEAKER_01]: I don't want them to pull that $15 million grant.

1433
01:52:57,817 --> 01:53:02,403
[SPEAKER_01]: So, I've had very good discussions with the mayor up to this point.

1434
01:53:03,203 --> 01:53:07,286
[SPEAKER_01]: I have appeared on a couple of occasions in front of the City Council.

1435
01:53:07,306 --> 01:53:13,510
[SPEAKER_01]: The last one, we discussed this project, and they seem to be very, very receptive.

1436
01:53:13,971 --> 01:53:27,380
[SPEAKER_01]: So I may be coming to the commissioners individually to seek your assistance in maybe lobbying the Council and the Mayor, but at this point, I don't think that's necessary.

1437
01:53:28,521 --> 01:53:28,781
[SPEAKER_09]: Okay.

1438
01:53:29,821 --> 01:53:31,302
